│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                   │
│ The transformation replaces a select guarded by an fcmp (<= 0.0) between -x   │
│ and x with a call to llvm.fabs. For NaN inputs, the original code returns the │
│ input x (here a signaling NaN with a specific sign bit), while fabs(x)        │
│ canonicalizes and clears the sign bit, changing the value. This violates      │
│ semantics unless we can prove that NaNs cannot occur.                         │
